	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am very pleased with the form and content of these latest situational events. However, i have quickly found it most disturbing that events aimed at lower level peeps are being farmed by high levels. Example... The halloween event in Qeynos Hills is obviously targeted for peeps between 5 and 25. The skellies that are part of the event are great xp for a person that would normally be hunting there. Yet every time i am there in the past couple days I see a group of 55+ peeps trying to farm Varsoon the Undying. Big deal, he drops a GBS and some other crap. Level 55+ peeps should be doing xp groups in velks/seb or helping with raids/epics, not KS'ing every damned mob that pops in a "special" scenario specifically intended for peeps much lower than you. @#%^s like you make me want to support TLC on all servers.<br><br>Friggin Pissed off Mage<br>(and no this post is not directed at the original poster)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
